  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Conference on the Regulation of International Recruitment</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project constitutes a contribution to the Global Conference for the Regulation of International Recruitment. The Conference took place in June 2019 and brought together 100 participants from over 30 countries around the world to discuss challenges, good practices and lessons learned related to recruitment regulation and the protection of migrant workers. Policy makers, regulators and recognized experts considered a range of themes, including the role of licensing, labour inspection, law enforcement, bilateral and multilateral cooperation, and migrant worker empowerment. Conference deliberations were captured for a new publication, The Montreal Recommendations on Recruitment: A Roadmap towards Better Regulation.</narrative>
  </description>
